# Cleanup-PR-1 manifest sidecars
#
# Each cleanup-script Apply-mode entry that references a sidecar
# (per_file_checksums_sidecar_path or permission_denied_sidecar_path)
# writes the sidecar file here. Sidecar filenames follow the pattern
# `<entry_id>.per_file.txt` and `<entry_id>.permission_denied.txt`.
#
# Sidecars are TRACKED so the audit trail is complete (per PR-1 iter 2
# Codex review). The .gitkeep file ensures this directory exists in the
# repo even when no sidecars have been written yet.
